para.paratext:
Regulatory statutes pertaining to sexual offenders not involving affirmative disability or restraint, such as the lifetime registration requirements imposed by the Penal Code, are subject to rational basis review upon an equal protection challenge, and the Legislature will be given wide latitude to decide who should be subject to registration requirements, since such regulatory statutes do not involve affirmative disability or restraint. People v. McKee (2010) 104 Cal.Rptr.3d 427, 47 Cal.4th 1172, 223 P.3d 566 , rehearing denied.
